org.batfish.bddreachability

Class BDDReachabilityAnalysisFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.batfish.bddreachability.BDDReachabilityAnalysisFactory

  • @ParametersAreNonnullByDefault
public final class BDDReachabilityAnalysisFactory
extends Object
    Constructs a the reachability graph for BDDReachabilityAnalysis. The graph is very similar to the NOD programs generated by DefaultTransitionGenerator. The public API is very simple: it provides two methods for constructing BDDReachabilityAnalysis, depending on whether or not you have a destination Ip constraint.

    The core of the implementation is the generateEdges() method and its many helpers, which generate the nodes and edges of the reachability graph. Each node represents a step of the routing process within some network device or between devices. The edges represent the flow of traffic between these steps. Each edge is labeled with a BDD that represents the set of packets that can traverse that edge. If the edge represents a source NAT, the edge will be labeled with the NAT rules (match conditions and set of pool IPs).

    To support MatchSrcInterface and OriginatingFromDevice ACL expressions, we maintain the invariant that whenever a packet is inside a node, it has a valid source (according to the BDDSourceManager of that node). For forward edges this is established by constraining to a single source. For backward edges it's established using BDDSourceManager.isValidValue(). When we exit the node (e.g. forward into another node or a disposition state, or backward into another node or an origination state), we erase the contraint on source by existential quantification.

        Parameters:
        srcIpSpaceAssignment - An assignment of active source locations to the corresponding source IpSpace.
        dstIpSpace - The destination IpSpace.
        forbiddenTransitNodes - A set of hostnames that must not be transited.
        requiredTransitNodes - A set of hostnames of which one must be transited.
        finalNodes - Find flows that stop at one of these nodes.
        actions - Find flows for which at least one trace has one of these actions.
